# Meet Attendance Backend

Node.js + Express backend for the Meet Attendance Tracker add-on.
Deployed on Google Cloud Run.

## Endpoints

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/attendance?conferenceId=xxx` | Returns real participants from Meet API |
| POST | `/api/save-to-sheets` | Saves attendance to Google Sheets |
| GET | `/` | Health check |

---

## Deployment to Cloud Run

### Prerequisites
- Google Cloud CLI installed: https://cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install
- Logged in: `gcloud auth login`
- Project set: `gcloud config set project the-yacht-group`

---

### Step 1 — Create a Service Account

```bash
gcloud iam service-accounts create meet-attendance-sa \
  --display-name="Meet Attendance Service Account"
```

### Step 2 — Grant required roles

```bash
# Meet API read access
gcloud projects add-iam-policy-binding the-yacht-group \
  --member="serviceAccount:meet-attendance-sa@the-yacht-group.iam.gserviceaccount.com" \
  --role="roles/meet.spaceViewer"

# Sheets write access (if using Sheets feature)
gcloud projects add-iam-policy-binding the-yacht-group \
  --member="serviceAccount:meet-attendance-sa@the-yacht-group.iam.gserviceaccount.com" \
  --role="roles/sheets.editor"
```

### Step 3 — Create your Google Sheet (for Sheets feature)

1. Go to sheets.google.com and create a new blank sheet
2. Copy the Sheet ID from the URL:
   `https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/SHEET_ID_HERE/edit`
3. Share the sheet with the service account email:
   `meet-attendance-sa@the-yacht-group.iam.gserviceaccount.com`
   (give it Editor access)

### Step 4 — Deploy to Cloud Run

```bash
gcloud run deploy meet-attendance-backend \
  --source . \
  --region us-central1 \
  --service-account meet-attendance-sa@the-yacht-group.iam.gserviceaccount.com \
  --set-env-vars SHEET_ID=YOUR_SHEET_ID_HERE \
  --allow-unauthenticated \
  --project the-yacht-group
```

This builds the Docker image, pushes to Artifact Registry, and deploys.
Takes about 2-3 minutes. You'll get a URL like:
```
https://meet-attendance-backend-xxxxxxxx-uc.a.run.app
```

### Step 5 — Update index.html with backend URL

In your `meet-attendance-addon` repo, open `index.html` and find:
```js
state.backendUrl = '/api';
```
Change it to:
```js
state.backendUrl = 'https://meet-attendance-backend-xxxxxxxx-uc.a.run.app/api';
```
Then commit and push.

