## Local Development

```bash
npm install

# Set up credentials locally
export GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=path/to/service-account-key.json
export SHEET_ID=your_sheet_id

npm run dev
# Server runs on http://localhost:8080
```

---

## Notes on Conference ID

The Meet SDK returns a `conferenceId` which is the meeting code (e.g. `abc-defg-hij`).
The Meet REST API uses this to look up `conferenceRecords`.
Note: `conferenceRecords` are only available AFTER a meeting starts and may have a
short delay. If participants show empty, wait 30-60 seconds after joining and refresh.